<subSubSection pageId="138" pageNumber="139" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="138.[151,1437,319,1497]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,860,885]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1912" box="[580,734,860,885]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[580,734,860,885]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Platytyphlops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble 
<emphasis box="[853,1021,860,885]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Sars" authorityYear="1887" box="[853,1017,860,885]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Paralamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Paralamprops</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but possess a maxillule palp with 2 setae, and those for which the state of the palp is unknown. When 
<bibRefCitation author="Sars, G. O." box="[896,1026,896,920]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" pagination="1 - 78" refId="ref129727" refString="Sars, G. O. (1887) Report on the Cumacea collected by H. M. S. Challenger during the years 1873 - 1876. Voyage of the H. M. S. Challenger, Zoology, 19 (55), 1 - 78." type="journal article" year="1887">Sars (1887)</bibRefCitation>
established 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Sars" authorityYear="1887" box="[1165,1326,895,920]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Paralamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1165,1326,895,920]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Paralamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, he noted the unusual absence of the maxillule palp. Despite this, species with a palp were ascribed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Sars" authorityYear="1887" box="[1180,1341,932,957]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Paralamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1180,1341,932,957]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Paralamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fage, L." pageId="138" pageNumber="139" pagination="3 - 47" refId="ref127186" refString="Fage, L. (1929) Cumaces et Leptostraces provenant des campagnes de SAS le Prince Albert Ier de Monaco. Resultats des Campagnes Scientifiques Accomplies Sur Son Yacht par Albert Ier, 77, 3 - 47." type="journal article" year="1929">Fage (1929)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gamo, S." box="[241,394,968,992]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" pagination="21 - 25" refId="ref127347" refString="Gamo, S. (1984) A new abyssal cumacean, Paralamprops corrolifera sp. n. (Crustacea) from East of the Japan Trench. Bulletin Biogeographic Society of Japan, 39, 21 - 25." type="journal article" year="1984">Gamô (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Day, J." box="[407,539,968,992]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" pagination="137 - 189" refId="ref127096" refString="Day, J. (1978) South African Cumacea, Part 3: Families Lampropidae and Ceratocumatidae. Annals of the South African Museum, 76, 137 - 189." type="journal article" year="1978">Day (1978)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Petrescu, I. &amp; Wittmann, K. J." box="[552,881,967,992]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" pagination="557 - 630" refId="ref129387" refString="Petrescu, I. &amp; Wittmann, K. J. (2003) Elements for a revision and notes on bionomy of the Cumacea (Crustacea: Peracarida) of the Weddell Sea, Antarctica. Zoologische Mededelingen, Leiden, 77, 557 - 630." type="journal article" year="2003">Petrescu &amp; Wittmann (2003)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones, N. S." box="[942,1091,968,992]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" pagination="33 - 46" refId="ref128526" refString="Jones, N. S. (1971) The fauna of the Ross Sea, Part 8. New Zealand Department of Scientific and Industrial Research Bulletin, 206, 33 - 46." type="journal article" year="1971">Jones (1971)</bibRefCitation>
. Most of these authors did not address the issue of the palp, ignoring the absence of the palp as a defining character for the genus. 
<bibRefCitation author="Calman, W. T." box="[1267,1436,1004,1029]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" pagination="603 - 676" refId="ref126444" refString="Calman, W. T. (1912) The Crustacea of the Order Cumacea in the collection of the United States National Museum. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 41, 603 - 676. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.41 - 1876.603" type="journal article" year="1912">Calman (1912)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Day, J." box="[199,329,1040,1064]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" pagination="137 - 189" refId="ref127096" refString="Day, J. (1978) South African Cumacea, Part 3: Families Lampropidae and Ceratocumatidae. Annals of the South African Museum, 76, 137 - 189." type="journal article" year="1978">Day (1978)</bibRefCitation>
did address the issue of the palp, acknowledging the taxonomic significance of the palp absence. However, while both 
<bibRefCitation author="Calman, W. T." box="[398,569,1076,1101]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" pagination="603 - 676" refId="ref126444" refString="Calman, W. T. (1912) The Crustacea of the Order Cumacea in the collection of the United States National Museum. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 41, 603 - 676. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.41 - 1876.603" type="journal article" year="1912">Calman (1912)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Day, J." box="[628,758,1076,1101]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" pagination="137 - 189" refId="ref127096" refString="Day, J. (1978) South African Cumacea, Part 3: Families Lampropidae and Ceratocumatidae. Annals of the South African Museum, 76, 137 - 189." type="journal article" year="1978">Day (1978)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Sars" authorityYear="1887" box="[938,1099,1076,1101]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Paralamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[938,1099,1076,1101]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Paralamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be separated into two genera, those with and without the palp, neither of them did so, and in fact Day synonymized 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1912" box="[1252,1406,1111,1136]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1252,1406,1111,1136]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Platytyphlops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a genus with a maxillupe palp with 2 setae, with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Sars" authorityYear="1887" box="[681,842,1148,1173]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Paralamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[681,842,1148,1173]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Paralamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Day, J." box="[856,1003,1148,1172]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" pagination="137 - 189" refId="ref127096" refString="Day, J. (1978) South African Cumacea, Part 3: Families Lampropidae and Ceratocumatidae. Annals of the South African Museum, 76, 137 - 189." type="journal article" year="1978">Day’s (1978)</bibRefCitation>
justification for mixing species with a palp and without a palp in the genus 
<emphasis box="[567,849,1183,1208]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">
<taxonomicName box="[567,798,1183,1208]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Paralamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sensu">
Paralamprops 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[736,798,1185,1208]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" sensu="lato">sensu</taxonomicNameLabel>
</taxonomicName>
lato
</emphasis>
was the difficulty in accessing the character as well as the lack of information for some species. However, both of these difficulties exist for mature male characters used in generic definitions, when it is very common in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kroyer" authorityYear="1846" box="[810,914,1256,1280]" class="Malacostraca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Cumacea</taxonomicName>
to encounter only females or immature males. However, the male characters are utilized because they are seen as of considerable systematic value, as is the palp. In keeping with Sars’ (1887) original concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Sars" authorityYear="1887" box="[713,874,1327,1352]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Paralamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[713,874,1327,1352]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Paralamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as lacking a maxillule palp, all species placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Sars" authorityYear="1887" box="[151,312,1364,1389]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Paralamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,312,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Paralamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to date that possess the palp are removed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1912" box="[810,964,1364,1389]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[810,964,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Platytyphlops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As the basal state of the maxillule palp is to be present and with 2 setae, it is most conservative to assume that species in which the state of the palp is unknown possess a palp with 2 setae. Thus, species formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Sars" authorityYear="1887" box="[946,1107,1436,1461]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Paralamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[946,1107,1436,1461]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Paralamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which the state of the palp is unknown are also included in the genus.
</paragraph>
